Omens

The omens command reads the current divine balance of the world.

  omens
  portents

Omens never shows raw pressure numbers. It gives broad prophetic language about
whether Mitra, Gaea, or Set is ascendant. If no god has enough pressure to rule
the realm, the world is Godless and the omens are silent.

Omens also reports major active divine events, such as Holy Hour or Eclipse.
Use patron to inspect your personal pledge, rank, debt, and current avatar
charge modifier.

World states:

  Ascendant  One god has enough pressure to lead the others.
  Godless    No god has enough pressure to rule the realm.
  Eclipse    Set has dragged a temporary shadow across the cycle.
  Holy Hour  A god's hour is active and patron blessings may strengthen.

Omens are affected by tithes, shrine activity, pilgrimages, marked enemies,
and reputation-bearing deeds with clear divine meaning. The command
intentionally describes the state in prophetic language instead of showing raw
pressure numbers.

